## How to Use This Rule

**This rule applies automatically when audit commands are executed or user requests audit reports.**

**Agents should:**
1. Check if `/docs/audit/` exists, create if missing
2. Generate report filename using format: `{audit_type}_audit_MM-DD-YYYY.md`
3. Include timestamp in both filename and report content
4. Follow required report structure (Executive Summary, Findings, Action Items, Recommendations)
5. Save report to `/docs/audit/` directory
6. Include report location in command output

**Validation checklist:**
- [ ] `/docs/audit/` directory exists
- [ ] Report filename follows format: `{audit_type}_audit_MM-DD-YYYY.md`
- [ ] Report includes timestamp in content
- [ ] Report follows required structure
- [ ] Report saved to `/docs/audit/` (not `logs/`)
- [ ] Command output includes report location

---

*This rule ensures all audit reports are consistently saved, named, and structured for easy discovery and historical reference.*
